animal.description:
PART OF A BONDED PAIR WITH NEVADA.

Sierra and Nevada are two sweet terrier mixes that are estimated to be 7-8 months old and currently weigh approximately 40 pounds each. They will continue to grow but we don't know just how big they'll get so any adopter should be prepared to love them if they stay medium sized dogs or grow up to be large dogs. They are terrier mixes but we cannot speculate beyond that. 

Sierra and Nevada are reported to be human and dog friendly, potty trained though any adopter should be prepared for accidents until they get on a schedule and you get to know their signals, and ride well in the car. 

Sierra and Nevada were found abandoned together as pups. They were rescued by a kind family that got them vetted and now are looking for a forever family for the two so we are giving preference to applications that will commit to keeping Sierra and Nevada together.

UPDATE: Sierra (black) and Nevada (white/black) are an incredibly fun, bonded pair of girls who are terrier mixes, weighing 40 pounds each, and are estimated to be 7 months young. These two were found abandoned together as pups and the family that found them took them home, started their potty, crate, and obedience training, vetted them and are in good condition. These two are accustomed to living in a home and are a bit unsure as to why they are at a shelter. 

They both ride very well in a car and once at my house, they became full of life running through my house, playing with toys, playing with each other, and they had fun having lots of toys to play with. They especially enjoyed tearing the stuffing out of toys, but also were content with playing with a few ropes and bones. 

They are reported to be human and dog friendly (cats unknown) and appear to have a good start on their potty training as they knew the cues of "let's go potty", but they did have an accident in my home, but after all, they are puppies. So, they need some additional guidance with potty training, but seem to have a good head start on their training. 

They both are treat motivated and know their basic commands, and Nevada will try to get on top of your counters so she will need some guidance in that regard. But overall, they both appear to be very smart and I believe these two will made a great addition to any family who is willing to take on the commitment of two young pups. Preference will be given to those committed to keeping them together.
animal.name: Sierra

animal.description:
Meet Alexo, a two-year-old Belgian Malinois/Shepherd mix.

We aren't sure of all the breeds that go into Alexo, but we do know he is a handsome boy weighing in at 59 pounds and only has half a tail! Alexo is a little unsure of everything new, he needs some work on his leash training and it's pretty clear he didn't know his breed mix was known to be guarding dogs (lol). However, Alexo is intelligent and has some energy so regular exercise will be important as well as stimulating his brain so he doesn't get bored.

Please do your breed research before applying to adopt Alexo. Belgian Malinois mixes are a special breed of dog with special requirements. These dogs were bred to have a job, and without the right activity level/purpose they won't flourish and that can lead to issues down the road. These dogs are incredibly smart and need to be challenged both physically and mentally to really be happy. The Belgian Malinois is known to be vocal when excited and can be a bit mouthy at times, proper training is key to help your Malinois adjust to their new life. Belgian Malinois are a fun, athletic breed that many have fallen in love with over the years, but please keep their breed needs in mind if you are considering to add one to your household.

Alexo will be available for adoption on 2/2/2021 At 11:52 AM.

If you are interested in adopting this pet please fill out an adoption questionnaire at www.yakimahumane.org. A Yakima Humane Society staff member will contact you once your questionnaire has been received.

If you would like to adopt this pet you can fill out an online adoption form at www.yakimahumane.org. Please give the name and ID number for the animal you wish to adopt.
If you are thinking about adding a pet to your family, be a hero, please consider adopting a shelter pet and if you already have pets – for life’s sake – spay and neuter. Spaying and neutering your pets is the single most important thing you can do to help decrease our nations severe pet overpopulation.
*NOTE: Nearly 90% of the animals that come into our shelter are abandoned, neglected, traumatized, injured, or ill. We attempt to give our best assessment of the animal’s welfare and temperament. Unfortunately, due to lack of funding, volunteers, and resources our physical and mental assessment of the animal is not always 100% correct.

animal.description:
Meet Yodel. a one and a half-year-old Husky/German Shepherd mix.

Yodel is a happy boy who enjoys going for his walks, a 70 pounds he is a great size to be your jogging partner. Yodel prefers to keep a clean kennel, however, as his name suggests he can be a talkative chap often singing the song of his people. This boy isn't sure what he wasn't to do, but he wants to do something! Yodel gets very excited when he sees other dogs so we do recommend a meet and greet if you have another dog in your house, prior to adopting Yodel.

Please do your breed research before applying to adopt Yodel, Huskies and Husky mixes are a very special breed of dog with unique requirements. They require a securely fenced backyard as they often have the inclination to roam and can be great escape artists. They need active homes that will help them burn off some of that extra energy along with a home that will work with them and help them learn and maintain their manners as huskies can have a tendency to be stubborn and mouthy at times. Huskies can have strong prey drives, and while every dog is different, many huskies will chase cats and livestock. Grooming is also an important part of their routine, brushing them several times a week can help prevent their undercoat from matting and keep them looking their best. Huskies are a fun, active breed that many have fallen in love with over the years, but please keep their breed needs in mind if considering adding one to your household.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Gary! I was rescued in Puerto Rico, along with my littermates, before arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. I'm a young puppy with lots of energy and spunk! I love to run around and play! I'm friendly and happy and just want to get to know you. Aside from having tons of energy, sometimes I can be loud, as I don't know how to control my barking yet. You have to remember, I'm a lot like a baby and have not necessarily adapted to a schedule yet so you may find that I'm staying up in my crate at night, and sleeping during the day. I need lots of direction and training, and that doesn't just mean puppy pre-school classes. I need you to show me the right and wrong things to do. Please don't be mad if in the process I wind up chewing some of your belongings or if I have accidents in the house - I promise I will get the hang of things! I require LOTS of time, energy, and patience, but my sweet little face makes it all worth it! This is a learning curve for us both but I promise that if you put the time and energy into helping me grow big and strong, you'll wind up with a wonderful little best friend for life.

animal.description:
Stripe is a sweet 2 year old male Chihuahua who will melt your heart. Stripe comes from a history of likely being abused, before he found himself at a kill shelter in rural Louisiana. Luckily, he’s done with all of that, forever! 
While timid at first, once this little man (about 14 lbs) bonds with you, he will be at your side waiting to smother you with kisses. He will need a little time to come out of his shell but patience and a lot of treats will do the trick. He is potty trained, not a chewer and does not bark excessively. He really is the perfect companion for someone who is ready to give him the love he so much deserves.  
Stripe’s energy level is perfect. He loves to play with his chew toy, jump and run around but he will settle down just as quickly. He loves to snuggle so he is the perfect companion to watch tv on the sofa or in bed. He is good with other dogs, already neutered, up to date on all shots and heartworm negative! This means, it’s time for him to find his forever home! 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Age: 2 Months (as of 1/24/2021)
Weight: ~ 8 lbs (as of 1/24/2021)

This dog has been spayed/neutered, is up to date on shots, on heartworm preventative and is microchipped.

The HappyDays pups are here to bring joy to your life!

These puppies are playful, even-tempered, and very affectionate! The litter is three adorable girls - Marion, Joanie, and Lori Beth and four handsome boys - Fonzie, Howard, Chachi, and Richie. We are thinking these cute babies are an Australian Shepherd and Carolina Dog mix. This litter is named after the classic tv show Happy Days that aired in the 1970s - 1980s. The pups love all people including the two teenagers that are living in their foster home. They are friendly and playful with each other but we don't know how they are with new dogs, but given that they are so young we anticipate that they would get along with a new dog sibling well. Their current foster home has two cats and they seem interested and playful when they encounter them but we can't guarantee they will do well as they grow older with co-habitating cats. They love toys and are happy to chill with a squeaky ball or fun chew toy when not playing with you, and t

heir favorite play styles are wrestling or a fun round of chase.

The pups are pretty quiet but you might hear them bark when playing.
Though a fenced yard is an ideal place for your puppy to romp and play safely, if that's not an option then lots of daily leash walks and opportunities to play off leash is the next best thing.

Puppies are a lot of work and require a strong commitment to teaching them obedience and socializing them with other dogs and people. A well-mannered, obedient dog will be welcomed most anywhere you take him/her.
As the pups are still so young, they haven't yet started on potty training, crate training or leash training but think they will pick up these skills quickly as they seem very smart. All the HappyDays pups are eager to please, toy and treat motivated, so puppy training classes will be lots of fun!

Marion would love to find a forever family that has lots of time and patience to raise a puppy properly, and who has lots of extra time for loving and cuddles. Think Marion (or one of her littermates) may be perfect furry addition to your family? Fill out an application today!

HappyDays pup's Backstory: These pups came from an unplanned litter in Arkansas and have been in SOS foster care since birth. They are getting ready to make the ride to New England to meet their forever families!

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

Gender: Male

Breed: Beagle Mix

Weight: 38 lbs

Cat friendly: yes

Crate trained: yes, trained, but barks initially

To adopt, go to:
www.mendingspirits.org/apply-to-adopt.html

From the Foster Family: Billie is an absolute DREAM. He is gorgeous, sweet, calm, and very loving. He is wonderful with our resident dogs, including one of our dogs who tends to be very leery of other dogs. Although he is a beagle, the ONLY time I have ever heard him bark is when we put him in his kennel but he always stops within 5-10 min and then is calm and quiet. Although he can initially be cautious in new situations he warms up fast. In a very short time, he has COMPLETELY melted our hearts and will be incredibly difficult to say goodbye to. He will be an amazing lifelong companion for a very lucky family.

About Me: Hi everybody my name is Billie and I just made a very long trip from Alabama to MN to meet my furever family. One thing I can tell you is the Minnesota snow is AWESOME and I love to play outside in it. My favorite thing in the world is going for walks and my foster mom says I do really good on a leash. Since I came to MN I have learned how to walk upstairs, go potty outside, and EAT!! My mom says I was skin and bones when I got here but she has been fattening me up with lots of food and love. I love being near my humans and will be a loyal companion for anyone who shows me they love me. I don't know any commands or tricks yet but my mom says I'm really smart and will learn quickly. So if you have a little empty spot in your heart and think I'm just the right piece to fill it then contact Mending Spirits and tell them Billie sent ya!!!

Marley is roughly around 16 weeks. She is a sweet girl who is very active, smart, and would love to go on walks. We are currently working on house training and crate training. She is a playful girl who is looking for a family of her own and a home full of toys. 

Our adoption fee includes the spay/neuter, up to date vaccines, microchip, Interstate Health Certificate, and the transport service to get the new family pet to you. 

 Note: All dogs are located in foster homes in ALABAMA and will be transported NORTH AFTER ADOPTION. This means there is no way for a meet and greet before adoption. We try our best to give you honest personalities of the pup for you. We are more than happy to send videos, pictures, and even video chat so that you may have the connection with your pup before adoption. Please know that we can only guess breed and age of our rescues.

 All pets are delivered by a licensed transporter. 
The transportation company that we use is PETSLLC. They are well known and very professional. The link is listed, you are more than welcome to look and see what the closest drop off location is for you. 

http://www.petsllc.net/stops.php?route=9

 COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! If you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

 Please copy and paste the following URL for our adoption application:

 https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

 Please be advised that our volunteers are busy rescuing, transporting, and caring for our animals. We will respond to your application as soon as possible. Upon review of your application, the rescue in Alabama will contact you, so you can ask any specific questions that you may have. 

 If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement.

 We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Meet Legolas

Big dog fans we have a beauty for you!!  Legolas is a 91lb, one and a half year old pup.  
Foster says he loves to play with toys , the kids in the house and chew everything.  He loves to run; chase balls and loves men especially!  He goes crazy for them, its wild.  He will approach any male on the street, he will go up to them and jump on the for kisses and wants to be petted endlessly.   He will run towards the husband with kisses and affections but with doesn't act like that around the wife.   So she thinks he prefers males to females

He likes to spend a lot of time outside.   His current foster says he may do best with a family that has a backyard, which they don't have.  He loves long walks every few hours.  She was taking him out every few hours for 1.5 to 2 hours.  If it is less than that, he gets very antsy and pace.  If you have a doggy door even better!  He can come and go as he pleases :)   

When walking on a leash he does pull hard so he will need some work with walking.   

He has lived in a house with 3 children and did fine.

We don't know how he does with dogs or cats.   We are told when walking he shows interest in other dogs.  Unsure if he wants to play or pounce.

Off transport he was surrounded by other dogs and didn't seem overly interested in any of them.  But he may have been overwhelmed by the new sights, smells, cold weather etc.

He came to us from one of our shelter partners in Arkansas.   They said he was found by a lady on the side of the road so she stopped to help him and called animal control.  


Adoption Process:

- please fill out our adoption application: https://www.dayofthedogs.org/adoption-application

- one of our team members will get back to you. 

- our dogs can be seen by appointment only after an approved application has been received.

- Adoption fee helps to cover spay/neuter, initial vaccines, rabies, initial worming, and microchip.

-We cannot place holds on our dogs. Please do not contact us until you are prepared to adopt.

NOTE:  We are very good about updating the pet's profiles once adopted.  So no need to write us to ask "Is he/she still available?"  If the post is up, the dog is still available. 

About Us:
Day of the Dogs is a 501c3 nonprofit that is dedicated to helping shelters increase live release.  We coordinate 2 - 4 transports per month from TX, OK and AR to NW Indiana/Chicagoland area.  We do direct adoptions ourselves out of Dyer, IN area and partner with 12 other rescues and shelters in both IL and IN that are willing to help southern pets in need.   
We rely on donations to help fund our ongoing transports.  Please donate if you can.  Every dollar adds up and we are grateful for any help we can get: https://www.paypal.com/paypalme/DayoftheDogs

animal.description: Now that Apples puppies have all been weened and adopted, she gets to be her own dog in a very loving foster home! Apple herself is 2 years old and about 48 pounds full grown. Apple can be shy around new people, but when she gets to know you she is incredibly sweet. She is smart, and picks up new tricks in just a couple of days (as long as you have a treat handy). Apple is housebroken, has learned sit, and has improved on her recall skills. She is still a bit skittish with sudden noises or movements but is comforted by affection from humans. Apple was very skinny when we pulled her from the shelter so shes still working on filling in her frame! She is extremely athletic and would make a great jogging buddy. She can climb and jump very high with those long legs of her. Apple prefers to be around her humans and does howl and cry when she is left. She is working on her crate training and separation anxiety, and would prefer a home where people are more around to love on her! Apple is wonderful with other playful dogs and always loves to hang out with them. We are currently looking for an adopter or foster to adopt home for Apple with another medium to large size dog to play with, and a fenced in yard. She is so snuggly and loving and cant wait to share all her love in a forever home. Apple is up to date on vaccines and spayed! She is able to be adopted or go into a foster to adopt home.

animal.description:
VAIL. Vail is about 64 pounds, 2 years old and looks like a Great Pyrenees or Samoyed mix. He has been a wonderful dog inside the home, and an extra fluffy cuddle buddy. We rescued Vail from a Kentucky shelter where he was bound for euthanasia. The hustle and bustle of the city life hasnt been helping Vail decompress well. While at first he was excitedly greeting other dogs and people on walks, he has been growing more reactive to dogs. 

Inside, he is an excellent dog who is gentle, very relaxed and loves to just lounge around by his people or on the sofa. We believe he would do really well in a quiet home, preferably with a yard that he can explore, and with no other dogs or cats. A calmer surrounding can definitely help him gain more confidence and work on his leash manners. 

We know that in the right environment, with a savvy foster, or foster to adopt home, Vail will make great strides! If you think youre the right fit, without other animals, and can open your heart and home to help him, please apply at www.rescuecity.nyc or email foster@rescuecity.nyc!

This young mama dog was found in a bad situation with her three 7 month old pups. We are looking for a happy forever home for this sweetie so she can feel loved and spoiled instead of forgotten.

We all know her puppies will be adopted and she will be left behind. 

At our rescue never take the puppies without the mom!

She brought these babies into this world and she deserves a loving home as much as they do if not more as she lived in this situation longer and raised them.

We don’t want her to get looked over because she isn’t a puppy. As puppies grown into adult dogs and they need a family to make a gracy choice to adopt a dog that is harder to place simply because someone wants a few short months of “having a puppy” 

PLEASE GIVE THIS MOMMA DOG A LOVING HOME FILLED WITH KISSES AND MOVIE NIGHTS ON THE COUCH.

animal.description:
Coco came to us as an owner surrender. Reportedly, the owner was unable to care for her as she deserved. He further indicated he had been "unable to bond with her". Coco is about 7-10 months old. She is fully vetted, current on shots, spayed, and microchipped. She relates well with other dogs when properly introduced. She is energetic and requires redirection. She knows some simple commands such as sit, stay, come. Is able to walk on a leash without difficulty. When relating to humans she is somewhat impulsive but responds appropriately to redirection. Coco would benefit from an intermediate to experience adopter who can build up on the skills she already has. We are not sure how she relates to cats or very young children as we haven't had the opportunity to evaluate these areas. A fenced-in-yard and home visit are a must. NO exceptions will be made to these requirements. 

Our adoption process is somewhat different from other organizations as we dont engage in same-day adoptions. The reason why we dont is to prevent returns, or worse, abandonment.

It is our mission to be the voice for the voiceless. Each dog, cat, or horse that we adopt out has been promised a second chance for happiness and security. We take this promise very seriously. Each potential adopter is asked to complete a PRE-ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE. Following receipt and evaluation of this document we proceed to schedule what we have come to call a meet & greet. 

We travel up to 1.5 hours from our location to bring the pet to your home which allows you to see him/her in a secure environment without external distractions. It also allows us to observe the environment where the dog/cat will live and make sure that it provides all the required security to prevent as much as possible any accident. Given the extraordinary circumstances our country is experiencing we have now also instituted what we call "virtual home visits". 

Using technology for "good", we visit your household using a free app called Google Duo. You can install it for free on your smartphone and will allow us to have a "face-to-face" conversation as well as it will allow us to take a peek at your yard. This allows you to see the dog you are interested in, and us to evaluate your fenced-in-yard.

After the meet and greet (in your home, adhering to CDC guidelines, I will wear a mask and we will meet in your yard) and if the interaction between you and our dog appears to be a good fit, and you are still interested in our companion dog or cat, we will proceed to complete the formal ADOPTION CONTRACT (if you are an out of state resident: at this time you proceed to make a deposit toward the adoption fee of $100.00 total adoption fee is $275.00), local residents will proceed to complete the adoption donation at this time, For out of state residents the balance of the adoption fee is paid when the dog is delivered. Residents can cover the cost of the adoption donation in cash or check, out of state /local residents can also use PayPal to make the appropriate payment using our email address ycmad2733@gmail.com. 

We ask all of our potential adopters to read our adoption contract beforehand and welcome as many questions as you may have after reading it. https://onedrive.live.com/edit.aspx?cid=a25c7feb241f9ba4&page=view&resid=A25C7FEB241F9BA4!42229&parId=A25C7FEB241F9BA4!7128&app=Word

For out of state potential adopters, we always inquire how they plan on getting the dog/cat to their residence. Airline trips transporting dogs from the Tallahassee International airport is non-existent. The nearest airport is in Pensacola which is almost 3 hours from our location. In the past, Tennessee residents come to pick the dog by driving to a mutually agreeable location. Others have requested a transport company to bring the dog to them. A highly reliable company i: http://itsadogsliferescuetransport.org (239) 207.6978

During the summer, we complete home visits on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 3 to 4 pm, Wednesdays, from 10-11 am, or 3 to 4 pm. In winter, we complete the visits on the same days with a change in time, Tuesday, Wednesdays, and Thursdays from 2-3 pm, and Wednesdays from 10-11 am. Please let us know which one is more convenient for you.

Thanks for your interest in a rescue dog!

animal.breeds_label: German Shepherd Dog & Catahoula Leopard Dog Mix
animal.description:
Ares is a 2-3 year old shepherd/catahoula mix and weighs about 60 pounds.  He has a lovable, athletic, and striking presence.  
He is both house and crate trained, neutered and heartworm negative.  Although he has not been fully tested with other dogs or kids, he is extremely intelligent  and responds quickly to new commands.  He is barrier/leash reactive to other dogs currently, so we’re allowing him time to decompress.  
With consistency and commitment, he would make a great forever friend.  Ares loves an active lifestyle. He would make the perfect adventure buddy! 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.breeds_label: Labrador Retriever & Pit Bull Terrier Mix
animal.description:
Cocoa is a 9 week old adorable little Mutt. When the shelter in Texas first took them in, they labeled them at pit mixes, which happens a lot, but as they grow we are thinking less and less that they are pit mixes, but we are not sure. They look more like Lab mixes to us, but the truth of it is these pups are probably mixes of 5 or more breeds, so they are just adorable, happy, sweet, playful little mutts. We are guessing these pups will be about 45-55lbs when full grown. 

Cocoa is a sweet, adorable pup. He loves to play with his siblings and the teens in his foster home. He is doing well on potty training and seems to be very smart! He gets along with the bigger doggy in his foster home (a Lab) and has really been learning from her, it's super cute. Cocoa loves to romp around, play with toys, run around the yard, and give LOTS of snuggles during down time. He is the perfect little pup. He would do great in a home with another dog but it's not mandatory as he is a confident happy pup and would do great with an active family who doesn't have another dog as well. 

If you are interested in adopting Cocoa or one of his siblings, please fill out our adoption application at brighterdaysdogrescue.com

animal.description:
Laurel is a 2-3 year old adorable Beagle/Corgi mix.

Laurel was heavily pregnant and homeless when she was rescued from the streets of Oklahoma. She was the worlds best mama ever, raising four bright little girls with so much love and sending them on to their new forever homes when they grew up.

Now its time for Laurel to finally be the baby, she wants to find her own special someone to take her on adventures and be her forever companion. And she truly deserves it.

Laurel is a Beagle Corgi mix, which means she is both incredibly smart, friendly to everyone but undyingly loyal to those she loves, and even though she is a grown up, this girl knows how to have fun and be silly. Oh, and I cant forget to mention that she is a low rider model who loves long walks and hikes despite her short stature.

If you are interested in adding Laurel to your family, please fill out our adoption application at brighterdaysdogrescue.com

animal.description:
**WE ONLY DO HOME VISITS FOR ADOPTIONS NEAR BROWARD & PALM BEACH COUNTIES**

Slowly give a gentle hug to shy Adira. Her name means Strong, and Noble. We gave her this name to help her self-confidence. She is a retired breeder mama. Adira is 2 year old English BullGirl given up to a vets office who turned her over to our rescue. Her spirit has been hurt by her previous people, but her playful loving personality still pops out occasionally. She will play with her toys and then looks around to make sure she is allowed to have fun. She will run in the fenced yard galloping like a horse then suddenly stops to hide as if she thinks she shouldnt act happy! More and more she is opening to human love and her personality is starting to shine. She is absolutely loving and becoming more confident. She is puppy playful and has some puppy behavior she is working on. Adira weighs almost 50 lbs. She is very shy and timid so an adult home would be better suited for her needs. She needs a home where they will show her it's ok to trust and be loved. Loud noises scare her so soft-spoken people would be best. Adira does seem to like women better than men, only cowering to men she does not react, just tries to make herself as small as possible, covering her eyes. She will need some guidance, love, and patience in order for her to come out of her shell.

She needs a home with people who have experience with English bulldogs, understand all their breed characteristics and health concerns. She is healthy now but may have allergies or breathing issues in the future. We just want people to be prepared long term. She is good with smaller dogs and some taller dogs but she really prefers to be the only dog to ensure her feelings of safety. She does guard her food from other dogs so feeding separately would be necessary if you have another dog.

This dog's adoption fee is $900 to go towards their vetting (vaccines, spay/neuter, heartworm/Ehrlichia/Lyme test, fecal test, pre-op blood work, dental cleaning, and microchip as well as grooming if needed). If you are interested please fill out the adoption application For additional information regarding our adoption process, please check our FAQ's Page. 

 *All dogs in the care of Get a Life Pet Rescue live in loving foster homes while waiting for their perfect match. They don't live in cages or crates (unless there is a medical reason to do so.) They are treated as family pets while in our care. * All dogs in our care are fed premium brand holistic food as well as supplements and vitamins specific to each dog's needs. We don't buy inexpensive bulk dry kibble, our rescues are fed premium wet food diets as part of a comprehensive rehabilitation program to ensure maximum health.*All of our rescues receive complete quality vetting including full dental cleaning with pre-op bloodwork, spay/neuter, vaccines, and grooming. Dogs in need of specialized medicine will be seen by specialists, such as full cardiac workups, ophthalmologist visits, all suspicious lumps, and bumps are biopsied, and every medical need is transparent to potential adopters. *Once you adopt from Get a Life Pet Rescue, you become part of our compassionate family and we are here for you if a problem with your precious dog arises.

animal.description:
Cherry
2 years old
43 lbs 
Female 
Australian Cattle Dog

Are you looking for your fur-ever Valentine? I am! My name is Cherry. I was surrendered to a shelter in Texas when my owners moved and did not take me along. All I want is to be loved forever. No more disappointments. No more heartache. I will snuggle into your arms and just enjoy your company. I love endless belly rubs and giving soft kisses. I will follow you around and be your best companion. 

I LOVE playing with my tennis ball! I entertain myself but I also enjoy playing fetch. I would love a yard to run in and explore! I am getting used to walking on a leash as I forget a human is at the other end and tend to pull.

I am a bit scared of larger or more domineering dogs. So a calmer canine brother or sister is more my speed with which to be around. Little kids tend to make me a bit uncomfortable as I have to get used to sudden, unpredictable movements. I have not been exposed to cats so I am not sure about them.

I am completely housebroken and will respect your belongings. I can be crated but really prefer free reign of the home...after all it is ours, right 

My foster mom says one of her favorite things about me is how I look at her with such loving eyes.

If I sound like your perfect fur-ever Valentine please apply at https://www.nickelcitycaninerescue.org/adopt-a-dog or message the rescue if you are already pre-approved.

animal.description:
Meet our newest senior, sweet Todd!
Todd found himself at a rural shelter and never was reclaimed. The wonderful volunteers sent out a plea for help to get this sweet old man out of the shelter and into a nice soft bed! Its pretty clear he LOVES his new bed, In fact he loves it so much his foster mom is going to send it with him to his adoptive home!
If she didnt have so many stairs she would adopt him -that is the one requirement for him -he cant go up and downs stairs well so needs a home with no or minimal stairs. 
Todd is such a good boy. He loves to be with the adults or other dogs in the home. He spends most of the day sleeping. He is housebroken and walks well on leash. He sleeps through the night. He is happy to snuggle on the couch or lay at your feet. He is very quiet. He loves taking his meds with cheese. He really is a great companion. He is an angel. 
Todd is best guess 10-11 years old, a 25lb mixed breed. Other than arthritis he is very healthy!

animal.description:
Sweet senior Momma Holly is too old to be a mom at 10-11 years old. Shes not too old however to make an amazing companion for a nice quiet home where she can live out her senior years. She would love a dog companion, few stairs, and a nice orthopedic dog bed. She is oh so sweet, timid, and full of love. Her babies are currently being bottle fed. 
You can learn more about her rescue here:

https://www.nbc4i.com/video/stop-the-suffering-interview/6243719/

Holly is best guess a 10-11 year old, 55lb senior German Shorthaired Pointer mix. She may have applications in progress but is currently available. We will have more information once he or she settles in and we get to know her better. 

Adoption fee is $195 and includes spay/neuter, microchip, fecal/deworming, vaccines and prevention up to date. Ohio residents only.

STS is a foster-based and volunteer-run rescue. We do not have a physical location or set hours for you to meet dogs, and it does take time to answer each inquiry. All dogs are in foster homes and once an application is approved and a home visit is completed you will be able to schedule meet and greets with available dogs. We encourage interested individuals to get approved prior to searching as it helps expedite the process. A Petfinder inquiry is not a substitute for an application. For detailed information about our adoption process, including fees, please visit our website at http://www.stopthesuffering.org.

animal.description:
Onyx is a 4yr old, 19lb Schipperke Corgi blend male. This pup has beauty and brains. His foster momma raves about how quickly he learns, and she says hes doing great learning basic commands. He needs an adopter who will spend the time continuing to train him so he can keep working on his doggy manners. Onyx is a fast, high energy dog and needs a safe environment to get his energy out. His new home MUST have a securely fenced yard as he should be treated as a flight risk. He walks well on a leash and likes to go for very long walks. He loves to play and can be a little rough. Absolutely no kids, dogs, or cats in the home. He has shown food and toy aggression when his foster mom has tried to take something away from his mouth. She believes training will help this. 

Onyx is still learning to trust his life in a loving home. He would prefer if his adopter is home more often than not since he does have some anxiety. Onyx does great with housetraining when kept on a schedule. 

Can you give this gorgeous guy the right forever home? If you are interested in adopting Onyx, please fill out the adoption application at www.PoodleandPoochRescue.org and well see if its a match. Onyx is up to date on vaccines, neutered, heart worm negative, and microchipped. His adoption donation is $350.

animal.description:
Lana is a one yr old, 35 lb., black and white Lab-Terrier mix. She is a recent arrival from Texas. We will add more about her as we get to know her. 

The adoption fee is $300 and covers age appropriate vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter.

 Applications are typically worked in time stamp order based on date/time of submission. If you have other dogs in your home, they must all meet the potential adoptee. It may save you a trip to bring them with you when you visit, if you are certain you want to adopt a new family member. 

*****We are currently operating by appointment only during the social distancing stage of quarantine. If you want to meet this pet, or are interested in adopting, please submit an inquiry or email to email@townandcountryhumanesociety.org.

Someone from the rescue will contact you and/or your family and determine, on a broad level, whether you might be a fit for the animal. If so, they will provide instructions for completing the application. Your application will be reviewed and you will be contacted to set up a time to meet at the shelter or the foster home. The introduction between you and the pet will be supervised by one of the dog counselors or the foster. If all goes well, you can adopt during the same visit.

Please be sure to follow us on Facebook to learn more about Town and Country Humane Society and our mission.

animal.description:
Welcome Jeanette!
She is part of our sister "chipmunk" trio!

Her and her sisters are a little over seven weeks old and doing great. These girls were being given away and we were able to save them thanks to a great supporter who contacted us. Their mom is for sure Husky, but dad we are still contemplating.

These girls are super sweet. They love to play, are very cuddly, love to lay on the couch and in their dog bed, and even have started howling as Husky’s do. They are great with kids, other dogs, and have been socialized very well.

Jeanette is the perfect combo of Momma and Dad. She has the Husky fluffy coat but then has some spots like Brittany.

She is very independent. She loves to play, pounce around, and is active. She can sometimes be hardheaded but she is overall, a sweet girl. 

We are looking for a home that has husky/large breed experience and has a large fenced in yard. If you are interested in one of these girls, and have any questions, you can contact their foster mom Allison at 225-938-6714 or just go straight to filling out an application at our website at www.danteshope.com

animal.description:
This old man is Franklin, he is around 15 years old... Yes you read that right. Franklin is blind, he was found wandering around and bumping into cars and anything that was in his path. Franklin is 17lbs and would love to find a home to retire in, he would do best in a quiet home since he is blind and everything startles him. He needs a family that will be patient with him and help him to start navigating his new life. Once he is comfortable he loves cuddling. He could go to a home with another dog but they will need to be introduced VERY slowly. 

Franklin's adoption fee is $150. Due to Franklin's age he will be part of our Forever Foster program, this means that we will cover his medical for the rest of his life. 

If you are interested please submit an adoption at crossyourpaws.com.

If you have an application on file- please message us on Facebook -do not email! 

We are a 100% volunteer 501c3 and rely solely on donations of our supporters and volunteers. 

#cyprescue #kennyrosssubaru #subarulovespets

animal.description: Hazey is a gorgeous 2 year old pit bull that is a very sweet girl. She has lots of energy and loves to play. Hazey is good with other dogs and kids. Cats are unknown. She rides well in a car and also on a 4-wheeler. She is leash trained, but pulls when she gets excited. Vacuums and baths are definitely not her favorite things! Hazey is vaccinated and house trained. She is scheduled for her spay and will be available for adoption after her surgery. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website - www.helpinghandsrescue.org.
